*****
[4] Cholera - Angola (Huila)
Date: Sun 30 Mar 2008
Source: AllAfrica & Angola Press Agency (Luanda) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200803310621.html>


At least 116 cases of cholera were recorded in the 1st quarter of
2008 at Chibia locality, south Huila province, 45 kilometers [28
miles] from Lubango city, without claiming lives. This was disclosed
to ANGOP, in Lubango, by the head of the local health division,
Sebastiao Antonio, who mentioned that 113 patients were discharged
after having been completely been recovered, whereas 3 are still hospitalised.

Sebastiao Antonio noted that 50 percent of the cases were registered
in Jau commune, and the others in the localities of Kihita, Capunda
Cavilongo and in the district headquarters. According to the health
official, at the moment the situation is stable, despite the number
of cases registered, since no deaths have been reported.

Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Huila in southwestern Angola can be found on a map of the country at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>. - Mod.LL]

[A similar report was submitted by Sidi Coulibaly
