[5] Cholera - Malawi (Blantyre)
Date: Sat 29 Mar 2008
Source: AllAfrica & Inter Press Service (Johannesburg) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200803290089.html>


Cholera used to occur mainly in the rainy season when contaminated
water entered the distribution system as a result of floods. Now,
there are instances of the disease throughout the year, as poor
hygiene is conducive to the spread of the _Vibrio cholerae_ bacterium.

Since the beginning of 2008 at least 8 people have died in a cholera
outbreak in areas around Blantyre, which is located in southern
Malawi. Up to 291 cases of cholera were reported within a 3 week
period in the region.

During a severe outbreak in 2002, more than 1000 people died of
cholera in Malawi.

[Byline: Pilirani Semu-Banda]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

