[6] Cholera - Mozambique (Nampula)
Date: Sat 29 Mar 2008
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=606084>


The health authorities in the northern Mozambican province of Nampula
have sent more doctors to strengthen the team in the Cholera
Treatment Center (CTC), in the provincial capital, Nampula City,
reports the Wed 26 Mar 2008 issue of the Maputo daily "Noticias."

Since the Nampula cholera outbreak began Saturday [22 Mar 2008], 29
people have been diagnosed with the disease, but so far no deaths
have been reported. The head of the community health services at the
Nampula provincial health directorate, Antonio Salimo, told reporters
that "20 patients are still receiving treatment at the Nampula CTC,
and 9 others have been discharged."

It was found that most of the cholera patients come from Nampula
neighborhoods, namely Namicopo, Muatala, Muhala, and Murrapaniua.
They were suffering from a serious shortage of clean drinking water
and poor sanitation conditions.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

